title: Did the 2020 elections run away from the end?
subtitle: Even with Joe Biden obtaining the majority of the election votes in the 2020 United States presidential election, President Donald Trump refused to give up.
author: Jessica Lee
vclaim: Until mid-November 2020, the American presidential election remained "out of sight," thus remaining a sufficient uncertainty about the outcome that United States President Donald Trump could reasonably claim that he might still be the winner.
